# Student Record Management System

This is a simple full-stack web application built using Java, ANSI SQL, HTML, and CSS.  
The system allows users to manage student records with basic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.

## Technologies Used

- Frontend: HTML, CSS  
- Backend: Java (JDBC, Servlets or basic Java classes)  
- Database: MySQL (ANSI SQL queries)  
- Server: Apache Tomcat (for deployment if using JSP/Servlets)

## Features

- Add new student records  
- View all student records in a structured format  
- Update existing student information  
- Delete records from the database  
- Simple and responsive UI using HTML & CSS

## How It Works

1. The frontend provides forms and tables to interact with data.
2. The backend Java code connects to MySQL using JDBC.
3. SQL queries follow ANSI standards for portability and simplicity.
4. Each action (add, view, update, delete) is handled by corresponding Java logic and SQL operations.
